In fact, I would be more likely to appreciate and value the unique perspectives and approaches of others, even if they are different from my own.

answer:   As an ENFP, I would rate the extent of my agreement with the statement as follows:

7 - Strongly Disagree

As an ENFP, I value creativity, spontaneity, and flexibility. I enjoy exploring new ideas and approaches, and I tend to be less focused on efficiency than other types.
